    <title>
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Feasibility Study - AIR TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT SYSTEM- ADVANCED MODERNIZATION PROGRAM, through Government of Latvia</narrative>
    </title>
    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">This $690,170 Technical Assistant (TA) activity supports Latvijas Gaisa Satiksme (LGS), the Latvian air traffic and navigation administrator, in its plans to overhaul, build up and modernize the technologies and practices comprising air traffic management (ATM) for Riga International Airport (RIA) and Latvian airspace as a whole. It will promote the use of U.S. exports in the modernization of RIA's facilities, the efficient handling of the increased air traffic that results from this, and the enhanced safety of Latvian airspace.</narrative>
    </description>
